      "content": "I can't advise you on taking medication without proper medical supervision, especially during pregnancy. I strongly recommend that you try to get in touch with your doctor or a new one as soon as possible to get a proper diagnosis and guidance. Taking Ciprofloxacin without a prescription can still pose risks to your baby, and using it without medical supervision can lead to overuse or interactions with other medications. \n\nHowever, if you're feeling desperate, you can try contacting a nurse hotline, such as the Health Line in Quebec, or a Telemedicine service for non-emergency advice.",
